 club’s Cobham HQ. VANGUARD Real Madrid's players and staff went into quarantine on Thursday, Spain's La Liga paused its season and the NBA halted games indefinitely as the coronavirus pandemic rocked world sport. La Liga authorities took the decision to suspend matches in the top two divisions for two weeks after Real Madrid confirmed its senior football team was… March 12, 2020 In "Sports" Arsenal manager Mikel Arteta has tested positive for the coronavirus, prompting the Premier League to announce they will hold an emergency meeting on Friday to discuss future fixtures. Arsenal have closed their training ground as a result of Arteta's positive test, with Gunners players and club staff who had recent… March 12, 2020 In "Sports" Spanish tenor Placido Domingo and disgraced Hollywood mogul Harvey Weinstein have joined the growing list of the rich, famous and powerful hit by the coronavirus. Here is a roundup: - Politics - Prince Albert II of Monaco has tested positive, although there are "no concerns for his health" the palace… March 23, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"